sbol:Collection.dcterms:title: iGEM Parts Registry
sbol:Collection.dcterms:description: The iGEM Registry is a growing collection of genetic parts that can be mixed and matched to build synthetic biology devices and systems. As part of the synthetic biology community's efforts to make biology easier to engineer, it provides a source of genetic parts to iGEM teams and academic labs.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: pSB3K5
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: Low to medium copy BioBrick standard vector
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: pSB3K5 is a low to medium copy plasmid based with kanamycin resistance. It has a p15A-derived replication origin. pSB3K5 is derived from the BioBricks vector scaffold BBa_I51001.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Reshma Shetty
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: BBa_I51001 BioBricks vector scaffold, p15A based origin and a version of the kanamycin resistance cassette that has been cleaned of restriction sites.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: Suffix
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This part is the standard BioBricks suffix.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Reshma Shetty

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: TOPO
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Insertion of this site will enable generation of a TOPO vector. The vector will have a T overhang and permit binding of topoisomerase I for direct cloning of PCR products. See http://openwetware.org/wiki/Topoisomerase_I_mediated_TA_cloning for a complete description of Topoisomerase I mediated cloning. This site belongs 3' of the cloning site. It is the reverse complement of BBa_B0043.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Reshma Shetty

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: TSS
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This part contains a stop codon in all 6 reading frames. Useful for ensuring that translation does not proceed through this part.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Reshma Shetty

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_B0054
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Terminator to be placed downstream of multiple cloning site in new pSB series plasmids. Similar to BBa_B0051.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Reshma Shetty

sbol:SequenceAnnotation.dcterms:title: identical to E. coli MG1655 between tonB and yciA

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: VR
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: Reverse BioBrick primer annealing site (VR binding site)
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This is the VR sequence to be used in construction of plasmids which include the VR primer site. It is the reverse complement of BBa_G00101.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Reshma Shetty

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_B0062
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Reverse of B0052, E.coli transcriptional terminator from the ribosomal RNA rrnC operon.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Caitlin Conboy

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: p15A
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: p15A origin of replication which is supposed to have low to medium copy number. It is also the origin of replication in pSB3* series plasmids.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Reshma Shetty
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: This part was constructed by PCR amplification of pSB3K3-P1010.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: The boundaries of this part are quite liberal to ensure that this part is a functional origin.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: SX scar
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: XbaI/SpeI mixed site. Simply used to aid in entry of parts into the registry.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Reshma Shetty

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: kanR
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Kanamycin resistance cassette for modular BioBricks vector construction.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Reshma Shetty

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: scar
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: NheI/SpeI mixed site. Used to help enter parts into the registry.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Reshma Shetty

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_B0053
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Terminator from the E.coli His operon
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Caitlin Conboy

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: VF2
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: Forward primer for sequencing/amplifying BioBrick parts (VF2)
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Originally named VF2, primer binds upstream of the standard BBa_MCS on biobrick vectors.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Tom Knight

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_B0055
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Terminator to be placed upstream of multiple cloning site in new pSB series plasmids.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Reshma Shetty
